    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required gradation level. One factor (Test conditions) achieves Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2; this shortfall is accepted at the Medium model risk level because the COU is explicitly scoped to ASTM F1717 standard conditions and no extrapolation beyond those conditions is claimed. QoI comparisons satisfy all pre-specified acceptance bounds (<10% difference, E/uval < 1.96) across all three quantities of interest and all eleven test constructs. The overall credibility of the simulation evidence is sufficient to support the Accepted decision for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending COU.",
